Webinar broadcast date: Wednesday, 28 October 2020 08h00 New York | 12h00 GMT | 12h00 London | 13h00 Paris | 13h00 Amsterdam | 14h00 Johannesburg | 17h30 New Delhi | 20h00 Singapore | 23h00 Melbourne With precious metal prices hitting record levels, and the aftermath of COVID-19 still being felt, mine owners are looking at maximising their production. High capital costs and long lead times to bring new shafts into production has further emphasised the focus on short term gains to help fund long-term investments in new infrastructure. That short-term focus is on upgrading existing infrastructure. This brings a renewed focus on refurbishing old assets and channelling capital to debottleneck and upgrade shaft and mine projects. Join UMS Group and Mining Review Africa for a webinar that will address the challenge of de-bottlenecking vertical shafts to maximise production. This webinar will discuss: Confirmed speaker: To be confirmed.